1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:08,000
C&C Generals: Zero Hour — Archipelago Mod

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Archipelago is a multiworld randomizer framework.
Items found in one game can unlock progress in another.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:28,000
This mod integrates Zero Hour into that network.
Units, buildings, and upgrades become randomized items.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Enemy unit clusters are spawned at map locations.
Defeating them sends "checks" back to the network.

5
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:48,000
This is an engine-level mod — 4,400 lines of C++
built on a modernized source port. Not a map hack.

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Everything you're about to see is running
in real-time in the game engine.

7
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:10,000
You start with almost nothing.
Basic infantry, dozers, and supply buildings.

8
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Everything else is locked until the
Archipelago network delivers it. Every seed is different.

9
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Unlocks are cross-faction — one item unlocks
the equivalent for USA, China, and GLA.

10
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Items arrive from the Archipelago network.
New unit categories appear in the build menu.

11
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:49,000
29 unlock groups cover the full roster — infantry,
vehicles, tanks, aircraft, upgrades, and buildings.

12
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Enemy unit clusters are spawned at fixed map positions.
These are the Archipelago checks.

13
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Each cluster is a coordinated group.
They guard a position and fight as a team.

14
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Hover over a unit to see its check ID.
Destroying the cluster completes the check.

15
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Attack one unit and the entire cluster retaliates.
They coordinate as a group.

16
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Each unit has a two-tier leash — a soft defend radius
and a hard max chase limit.

17
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Beyond the chase limit, units always retreat —
faster movement, healing, and damage reduction.

18
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:54,000
After retreating, a 5-second cooldown prevents
them from immediately re-engaging.

19
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:04,000
With all items received, the full roster unlocks —
over 300 unit and building templates.

20
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Time to test the limits of the
spawned unit protection system.

21
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Spawned clusters are protected by a 91-rule damage matrix.
Superweapons deal zero damage.

22
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:27,000
They're immune to EMP, hijack,
hacker disable, and sniper vehicle kills.

23
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:36,000
4x health, 140% weapon range, and built-in stealth detection.
These are not easy targets.

24
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:45,000
To complete a check, defeat the cluster
with conventional firepower — no shortcuts.

25
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Each completed check sends an item into the
Archipelago network — for you or another player.

26
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Work in progress. The Archipelago network connection
is next — this demo uses local test fixtures.

27
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Built on the open-source SuperHackers engine port.
Follow the project for updates.
